# Proxy and guard

- Preflight runs budget + loop checks in parallel before upstream
- Headers: `X-TokenGuard-API-Key` / `X-TokenGuard-Key`, `X-TokenGuard-Provider`, `X-TokenGuard-Session-ID`
- Block codes: `402` budget, `409` loop, `503` deps down, `401` missing key, `413` oversized body
- After success: count tokens (incl. SSE via `stream_counter.go`), settle reservation, log usage
- Mgmt: constant-time admin secret compare; CORS only on `/mgmt/*` (not proxy errors)
- Provider routes come from env map; do not hardcode provider host lists in handlers

When changing guard flow, update tests in `proxy_test.go` and docs in `docs/API.md` if status codes or headers change.
